author: Amy Kuperinsky | NJ Advance Media for NJ.com
title: Fetty Wap album expected to debut at No. 1 on Billboard chart
text:
Fetty Wap 's first album is on track to debut at No. 1 on the Billboard 200 chart, Billboard reports.
The Paterson native's self-titled debut album was released on Sept. 25 from RGF (Real Good Fellas) Productions and 300 Entertainment, a label distributed by Atlantic Records.
RELATED: Fetty Wap hospitalized following N.J. motorcycle crash Fetty Wap, born Willie Maxwell II, rose to fame this year after hitting it big with his debut single, " Trap Queen ," which peaked at No. 2 on the Hot 100 chart in May.
Maxwell, 24, then achieved the rare feat (one claimed by the Beatles decades before him, but higher up the chart) of having his first three consecutive singles â€” "Trap Queen," " My Way " and "679" â€” simultaneously rank in the top 11.
Billboard reports the "Fetty Wap" album could see sales of 110,000 units for the week ended Oct. 2.
RELATED: Fetty Wap album review The day after his album came out, Maxwell was injured in a motorcycle crash in Paterson, and later said he had broken his leg . Police issued the hip-hop artist three summonses, for failure to provide a license to drive a motorcycle and failure to provide registration and proof of insurance. After news of Maxwell's collision with a car spread on social media, tweets expressing support for him and relaying news of the incident made #PrayForFetty a worldwide Twitter trend.
